    <h>loch</h>
    <p><g>loch</g>
        <en>lake</en> is a masculine <a href="?xx=nouns/simple_common_nouns">simple common
        noun</a>.</p>

    <p>Examples of <g>loch</g> as the complement of the preposition <a href="?gd=air"><g>air</g></a>
        <en>on</en> – <ul>
            <li>pre-specified – <ul>
                    <li>definite article – <g>air an loch</g>
                        <en>on the river</en> – <ul>
                            <li>unmodified – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>An robh Calum ag iasgach air an loch an dé? Bha.</gd>
                                        <tr>Was Malcolm fishing on the lake yesterday? Yes, he
                                            was.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Có bha ag iasgach air an loch? Bha Calum.</gd>
                                        <tr>Who was fishing on the lake? Calum was.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>




